hopobject.body: Could I ask who's calling? h2go water bottle review Churchill, launched in March 2009, is structured to issue USD-denominated CP up to a maximum aggregate amount of USD40bn. CP is issued to fund the purchase of eligible assets and all assets funded by Churchill are fully supported by transaction-specific liquidity facilities. Churchill also has the ability to issue extendible notes with a tenor of up to 185 days. As at end-June 2013, Churchill had USD3.5bn of CP outstanding
